SIMPLE: kneeler
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kneeler
<hw>Kneel"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
kneels or who worships by or while kneeling.</def>
<rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A cushion or stool to kneel on, such as one attached
to a pew in a church.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>A name given to certain
catechumens and penitents who were permitted to join only in parts of
church worship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kneelingly</ent>⟦br⟧
